e3-convert-xunit: add handling for classname attributes

See merge request it/e3-testsuite!18

e3-convert-xunit: add handling for classname attributes

If testcases have an associated class name, include that class name in
the name used for that test in the produced report. This will help
distinguishing homonym tests in testsuites based on classes.

Merge branch 'trojanek/dontwalk' into 'master'

Don't walk into internal VCS directories when looking for tests

See merge request it/e3-testsuite!15

Don't walk into internal VCS directories when looking for tests

Added test, without the patch, would cause multiple failures when
running the tox command on e3-testsuite itself, e.g. from the TestBasic
in test_basics.py, which expects simple-tests directory to contain just
test1 and test2. With the patch this test provides coverage for added
code. There is no additional expected output.

We could add a similar test for the ".svn" directory, but not for
".git", because git doesn't repositories to contain ".git" directories.
For coverage and testing the "CVS" directory is enough.
